WEBVTT

00:00.968 --> 00:04.702
[grunting and groaning]

00:04.771 --> 00:09.674
Scootaloo, is this
such a good idea?

00:09.743 --> 00:11.209
What are you talking about?

00:11.278 --> 00:13.312
This is the best
idea I've ever had!

00:14.648 --> 00:16.414
It's just--

00:16.483 --> 00:19.317
--You wanna come. But
we talked about this.

00:19.386 --> 00:21.653
Non-Pegasus ponies fall
through the clouds.

00:24.258 --> 00:25.790
Right, but--

00:25.859 --> 00:28.359
I think we're good.

00:28.428 --> 00:30.161
We are?

00:30.230 --> 00:32.597
Scootaloo, I know you
have to go to Cloudsdale

00:32.666 --> 00:34.766
to finish your report;
I'm just wondering

00:34.835 --> 00:37.368
if this is the best
way to get there

00:37.437 --> 00:40.772
It'll be fine. Besides,
how else could I get there?

00:40.841 --> 00:42.407
A Pegasus chariot.

00:42.476 --> 00:43.675
A flock of birds!

00:43.744 --> 00:45.310
A hot air balloon.

00:45.379 --> 00:48.279
Huh, those do seem a lot safer.

00:48.348 --> 00:49.747
Maybe I should try
to find another--

00:49.816 --> 00:50.815
--WAAAAYY!

00:50.884 --> 00:54.319
♪♪

00:54.388 --> 00:55.420
WOOHOO!

00:55.489 --> 00:59.224
♪♪

00:59.293 --> 01:00.758
[grunt]

01:00.827 --> 01:02.294
Nailed it.

01:05.499 --> 01:07.299
Little ma'am, are
you all right?

01:09.203 --> 01:10.335
[gasp]

01:10.404 --> 01:13.671
♪♪

01:13.740 --> 01:19.111
You're-- you're-- you're
Rainbow Dash's dad!

01:21.315 --> 01:24.116
Ah yes. Bow Hothoof
at your service.

01:25.519 --> 01:30.289
[long shriek]

01:33.360 --> 01:36.661
<i>♪ My little pony,</i>
<i>my little pony ♪</i>

01:36.730 --> 01:39.230
<i>♪ Aaaahhh ♪</i>

01:39.299 --> 01:41.332
<i>♪ My little Pony ♪</i>

01:41.401 --> 01:43.234
<i>♪ I used to wonder what</i>
<i>friendship could be. ♪</i>

01:43.303 --> 01:45.003
<i>♪ My Little Pony ♪</i>

01:45.071 --> 01:47.572
<i>♪ Until you all shared</i>
<i>its magic with me. ♪</i>

01:47.641 --> 01:49.374
<i>♪ Big adventure! ♪</i>
<i>♪ Tons of fun ♪</i>

01:49.443 --> 01:51.209
<i>♪ A beautiful heart! ♪ ♪</i>
<i>Faithful and strong! ♪</i>

01:51.278 --> 01:53.712
<i>♪ Sharing kindness ♪</i>
<i>♪ it's an easy feat ♪</i>

01:53.781 --> 01:55.914
<i>♪ And magic makes it</i>
<i>all complete! ♪</i>

01:55.983 --> 01:58.216
<i>♪ To have my little pony ♪</i>

01:58.285 --> 02:01.553
<i>♪ Do you know you're all</i>
<i>my very best friends? ♪</i>

02:01.622 --> 02:03.555
♪♪

02:08.528 --> 02:11.729
[long shriek continues]

02:11.798 --> 02:14.700
Um, honey, something's
going on out here!

02:19.473 --> 02:22.340
[higher shriek]

02:22.409 --> 02:25.877
Heavens to Celestia,
what's wrong with her?!

02:25.946 --> 02:30.582
I don't know, but you
just made it worse.

02:30.651 --> 02:35.453
Sorry, it's just, you're
Rainbow Dash's parents!

02:35.522 --> 02:38.423
[long scream]

02:38.492 --> 02:39.924
She's doing it again!

02:39.993 --> 02:41.893
[shriek continues]

02:41.962 --> 02:43.428
Oh, dearie, please.

02:43.497 --> 02:46.898
You might shatter my Princess
Celestia commemorative plates!

02:46.967 --> 02:47.832
Agh!

02:47.901 --> 02:49.434
[scream continues]

02:49.503 --> 02:50.536
[shatter]

02:51.939 --> 02:56.274
I'm so sorry. I just... I
can't believe I'm meeting you.

02:56.343 --> 02:57.842
My name's Scootaloo and
I'm doing a school report

02:57.911 --> 02:59.244
on your daughter.

03:00.447 --> 03:02.513
Our Rainbow Dash?

03:02.582 --> 03:04.849
The report's on an
inspirational pony in my life.

03:04.918 --> 03:07.352
And no pony inspires
me more than she does.

03:09.723 --> 03:11.956
I'm putting together this
scrapbook for my report.

03:12.025 --> 03:14.525
I'm her biggest fan!

03:14.594 --> 03:17.962
Little trotter, what
you say is impossible...

03:18.031 --> 03:22.868
because nopony is a bigger fan
of our Rainbow Dash THAN US!

03:25.372 --> 03:29.841
Whoa. You always
wear that shirt?

03:29.910 --> 03:33.611
Actually it's laundry day,
but pretty great, right?

03:33.680 --> 03:35.446
Yeah!

03:35.515 --> 03:38.416
My name's Windy Whistles
and I just have to say

03:38.485 --> 03:40.785
that it is a total
blast to meet somepony

03:40.854 --> 03:44.055
that loves Rainbow
Dash as much as we do!

03:44.124 --> 03:45.457
What can we help
you with?

03:45.525 --> 03:48.559
Well, I know all about Rainbow
Dash's time in Ponyville,

03:48.628 --> 03:51.029
but I don't know anything
about her life before that.

03:51.098 --> 03:54.065
Well, you came to
the right place.

03:54.134 --> 03:56.534
♪♪

03:56.603 --> 03:57.469
[delighted gasp]

03:59.473 --> 04:03.374
Windy: Here you go. Rainbow
Dash's favorite meal.

04:03.443 --> 04:06.611
A pasta and potato
sandwich on sourdough!

04:06.680 --> 04:08.880
She just LOVES to carbo load!

04:08.949 --> 04:12.517
I can't believe I'm eating
Rainbow Dash's favorite food,

04:12.586 --> 04:14.886
made by Rainbow Dash's mom,

04:14.955 --> 04:18.389
while sitting in Rainbow
Dash's childhood kitchen!!

04:18.458 --> 04:22.460
This is the greatest
day of my life!

04:22.529 --> 04:23.394
[chomp]

04:23.463 --> 04:25.063
[munching]

04:25.132 --> 04:27.865
Mm! Mmmmm!

04:27.934 --> 04:31.002
I think it's time for
a tour of the house.

04:31.071 --> 04:32.937
OK!

04:33.006 --> 04:36.775
Our little Dashy was an early
learner and so rambunctious.

04:38.845 --> 04:39.944
The combination was...

04:40.013 --> 04:41.313
EXCITING!

04:44.084 --> 04:46.451
Wow.

04:46.520 --> 04:51.522
♪♪

04:51.591 --> 04:53.058
Is that her room?

04:55.629 --> 04:57.796
[scream]

04:59.032 --> 05:01.466
Rainbow Dash's linen closet!

05:01.535 --> 05:03.568
Her carpet!

05:03.637 --> 05:06.504
Her inspirational poster!

05:06.573 --> 05:09.640
"When the going gets tough,
the tough don't notice

05:09.709 --> 05:13.378
because they have hard shells."
That's so Rainbow Dash.

05:17.851 --> 05:19.784
Woohoo!

05:19.853 --> 05:22.521
Scootaloo, want to see
something really cool?

05:28.061 --> 05:35.466
<i>♪ [angelic choir] ♪</i>

05:35.535 --> 05:36.467
[gasp]

05:36.536 --> 05:40.438
♪♪

05:40.507 --> 05:41.740
[door closes/angel choir ends]

05:41.808 --> 05:44.709
I.. uhh.. installed the
sound effects myself.

05:44.778 --> 05:46.911
<i>♪ [angel choir] ♪</i>

05:46.980 --> 05:48.513
Pretty great, huh?

05:48.582 --> 05:49.781
So great!

05:49.850 --> 05:51.582
And look at this.

05:51.651 --> 05:55.153
She was wearing it when
she spoke her first words.

05:55.222 --> 05:57.022
So cool.

06:00.060 --> 06:03.562
And this broken lantern is from
when she first learned to fly.

06:06.199 --> 06:10.435
And this bitten apple is from
when she grew her first tooth.

06:10.504 --> 06:11.903
So many memories.

06:13.273 --> 06:16.207
You're so lucky to
have all of these.

06:16.276 --> 06:19.143
Well, I may have a
ton of Dash-mentos,

06:19.212 --> 06:20.945
but I don't have
any of those

06:21.014 --> 06:24.882
Rainbow Dash saves Ponyville
headlines like you.

06:24.951 --> 06:25.883
Tradesies?

06:25.952 --> 06:26.885
Dealsies!

06:31.591 --> 06:34.625
So where's all the
Wonderbolt stuff?

06:34.694 --> 06:37.662
You mean Rainbow Dash's
personal collection

06:37.731 --> 06:40.565
of Wonderbolt memorabilia?

06:40.634 --> 06:43.067
No, I mean where's all the
stuff about Rainbow Dash

06:43.136 --> 06:45.536
getting accepted into
the Wonderbolt Academy

06:45.605 --> 06:47.572
and then getting
chosen as a Wonderbolt.

06:50.043 --> 06:53.010
Wait, you don't know that
your daughter's a Wonderbolt?

06:53.079 --> 06:55.147
And I got to tell you!

06:58.118 --> 07:01.119
Oh, wow, you should see
your faces right now!

07:04.024 --> 07:05.457
See that's what your
faces look like.

07:11.031 --> 07:14.832
Our daughter's a WONDERBOLT?!

07:14.901 --> 07:16.534
<i>♪ [angel choir] ♪</i>

07:16.603 --> 07:17.668
[door closes]

07:17.737 --> 07:18.803
Great timing.

07:18.872 --> 07:19.937
Great door.

07:20.006 --> 07:24.175
I just... it's unbelievable.

07:24.244 --> 07:27.645
You two were kind enough to show
me the Rainbow Dash you know;

07:27.714 --> 07:31.616
now please, allow me to show
you the Rainbow Dash I know.

07:31.685 --> 07:41.225
♪♪

07:41.294 --> 07:43.194
Let's make some thunder!

07:43.263 --> 07:44.896
I was born to
make thunder!

07:46.600 --> 07:47.932
[thunderclap]

07:48.001 --> 07:49.233
[shouting]

07:49.302 --> 07:51.102
We've got turbulence!

07:51.171 --> 07:52.837
How? Where's it
coming from?

07:52.906 --> 07:54.272
[shouting]

07:54.341 --> 07:55.207
There!

07:55.275 --> 08:00.244
[encoura
ging
shouts]

08:00.313 --> 08:01.680
Oh, no.

08:03.783 --> 08:05.950
OK, which pony
broke protocol

08:06.019 --> 08:08.986
and invited guests to
our training exercises?

08:09.055 --> 08:11.188
I guess they're
with me.

08:11.257 --> 08:12.524
Agh!

08:14.728 --> 08:19.030
Mom, Dad, so good
to see you.

08:19.099 --> 08:22.767
Oh, honey it's so
great to see you, too!

08:22.836 --> 08:25.636
And WOW! You were so
amazing up there

08:25.705 --> 08:27.638
with all of that flying!

08:27.707 --> 08:29.974
How did you know
I was here?

08:30.043 --> 08:33.010
Scootaloo filled us
in on everything.

08:33.079 --> 08:35.013
You modest pony, you.

08:37.751 --> 08:40.251
I can't believe I'm
documenting the moment

08:40.320 --> 08:42.754
your parents first saw
you as a Wonderbolt!

08:45.191 --> 08:48.893
And these must be your
Wonderbolt friends.

08:48.962 --> 08:52.830
Hello team! I'm Windy Whistles,

08:52.899 --> 08:57.168
the mom of the best
Wonderbolt ever! Yeah!

08:57.237 --> 09:00.805
Just kidding, you guys
were great, too. Go team!

09:00.874 --> 09:02.306
Mom.

09:02.375 --> 09:03.908
[laugh]

09:03.977 --> 09:06.777
Hello Ma'am, nice
to meet you.

09:06.846 --> 09:12.316
Nice to meet you, as well and
love those goggles! Love 'em!

09:12.385 --> 09:14.885
You know I have
goggles, too,

09:14.954 --> 09:17.689
but they're mostly just for
swimming. Oh and bath time.

09:19.292 --> 09:23.794
Mom, please! They don't want
to hear about your bath time.

09:23.863 --> 09:27.932
I can't believe it. My
daughter, a Wonderbolt!

09:28.001 --> 09:29.967
So proud!

09:30.036 --> 09:33.204
Dad, hold it together!
We're in public.

09:33.273 --> 09:35.706
I know, I know, but it's just...

09:35.775 --> 09:38.776
you had a goal and
you achieved it.

09:38.845 --> 09:42.914
[blubbering]

09:45.051 --> 09:47.318
All right Wonderbolts,
let's hit the showers

09:47.387 --> 09:51.722
and give Rainbow Dash some
time to spend with her family.

09:51.791 --> 09:54.191
OK, yeah. Great practice.

09:54.260 --> 09:57.662
I'll uh, catch up with
you guys in a minute.

09:57.731 --> 10:01.032
Sir. You really
raised a great flyer.

10:01.101 --> 10:05.302
Oh, no... tears
welling up again!

10:05.371 --> 10:06.904
Dad.

10:06.973 --> 10:13.210
[blubbering]

10:13.279 --> 10:14.646
Could you give us a sec?

10:15.915 --> 10:17.415
Is something wrong?

10:17.484 --> 10:19.050
Yeah, you should
have warned me

10:19.119 --> 10:20.418
that you were
bringing my parents,

10:20.487 --> 10:24.221
or talked to Twilight or
something. Not just shown up!

10:24.290 --> 10:25.723
Why?

10:25.791 --> 10:29.093
It's just, my parents and I
have a delicate relationship.

10:29.162 --> 10:31.362
I love them very much
and we're really close,

10:31.431 --> 10:34.298
but there's a reason I didn't
tell them I'm a Wonderbolt.

10:34.367 --> 10:37.068
They can be a little
bit embarrassing.

10:37.137 --> 10:40.371
Huh? Really?

10:40.440 --> 10:42.440
Yeah, really.

10:42.509 --> 10:46.444
And now you've invited a whole
lot of crazy into my life!

10:46.513 --> 10:48.413
What's wrong with
a little support?

10:50.817 --> 10:53.951
♪♪

10:54.020 --> 10:55.920
Bow and Windy, I'd
like you to meet

10:55.989 --> 10:57.388
Apple Bloom and
Sweetie Belle.

10:57.457 --> 10:58.255
Hi!

10:58.324 --> 10:59.256
Hello!

10:59.325 --> 11:01.058
Greetings, small ponies.

11:01.127 --> 11:03.260
Are you excited to
see Rainbow Dash?

11:03.329 --> 11:05.730
Oh, my, YES!

11:05.799 --> 11:09.366
And to think we never bothered
to come to a Wonderbolt event.

11:09.435 --> 11:11.469
We said if Rainbow Dash
isn't a Wonderbolt,

11:11.538 --> 11:14.839
then what's the
point? But now she is!

11:14.908 --> 11:16.141
And she earned it!

11:17.977 --> 11:20.377
Did you know it all
started when she won a spot

11:20.446 --> 11:22.813
in the coveted
Wonderbolt Academy,

11:22.882 --> 11:25.149
training under Spitfire!

11:25.218 --> 11:29.019
I didn't know that.
How wonderful!

11:29.088 --> 11:32.056
But then she had some
heavy competition,

11:32.125 --> 11:36.026
especially against another
Pegasus named Lightning Dust.

11:36.095 --> 11:38.062
Oh, no...

11:38.131 --> 11:40.898
But of course, Rainbow
Dash proved to be the best

11:40.967 --> 11:43.934
and later made it into
the Wonderbolt Reserves!

11:44.003 --> 11:46.003
Hooray again!

11:46.072 --> 11:50.107
But a jealous ex-Wonderbolt,
Wind Rider, was worried

11:50.176 --> 11:53.043
that Rainbow Dash might
break his speed record

11:53.112 --> 11:57.114
and so he framed her for
a crime she didn't commit.

11:57.183 --> 11:59.817
Oh, no.

11:59.886 --> 12:02.820
But thanks to Rarity, Rainbow
Dash proved her innocence

12:02.889 --> 12:04.989
and became a back-up Wonderbolt.

12:05.058 --> 12:06.991
Until Fire Streak retired

12:07.060 --> 12:09.460
and she became an
official Wonderbolt!

12:09.529 --> 12:11.328
Hooray!

12:11.397 --> 12:14.465
Wow! What a gripping tale.

12:14.534 --> 12:17.034
You really know your
Rainbow Dash history.

12:17.103 --> 12:19.003
You're going to do
great on your report.

12:20.540 --> 12:21.506
Show's about to start!

12:23.409 --> 12:26.343
♪♪

12:26.412 --> 12:29.380
[zoom]

12:29.449 --> 12:31.415
HOO! HOO! HOO! HOO! HOO!

12:31.484 --> 12:35.219
Come on, bolts, LET'S
START THIS Thing!

12:35.288 --> 12:40.424
Wonderbolts Spring
Showcase HERE. WE. GOOOO!

12:40.493 --> 12:44.094
Rip it up and tear it down!

12:44.163 --> 12:47.832
Then build it back up again
and tear IT back down AGAIN!

12:47.901 --> 12:49.366
Yeah!

12:49.435 --> 12:51.836
Woo! Yeah! Uhuh!

12:51.905 --> 12:54.506
Go go go!Yes!

12:56.576 --> 13:01.011
GO RAINBOW DASH!
BEST WONDERBOLT EVER!

13:01.080 --> 13:03.848
Woohoo! That's my daughter!

13:03.917 --> 13:07.017
Go Rainbow! Go Dashy!
Go go go go go!

13:07.086 --> 13:10.888
[whoosh]

13:10.957 --> 13:14.292
Woohoo! You go, girl!

13:17.163 --> 13:19.063
Your folks were
definitely loud,

13:19.132 --> 13:20.498
but they weren't that bad.

13:21.601 --> 13:23.500
[explosion]

13:23.569 --> 13:27.104
Whoa, since when did we
add fireworks to the show?

13:27.173 --> 13:30.274
Uh...we didn't.

13:30.343 --> 13:34.111
Atta girl! Woohoo!
Yeah! Go girl! Go go go go!

13:34.180 --> 13:39.383
[explosions and whistling]

13:39.452 --> 13:40.585
Wow.

13:41.988 --> 13:47.925
[excited chatter]

13:47.994 --> 13:49.260
Go RAINBOW DASH!

13:51.631 --> 13:53.664
You sign that photo!

13:53.733 --> 13:55.033
Whoo!

13:58.037 --> 14:00.204
♪♪

14:00.273 --> 14:02.339
Cut the ribbon! Cut the
ribbon! Cut the ribbon!

14:02.408 --> 14:03.441
Cut the ribbon!

14:07.447 --> 14:10.347
The camera loves
you! Yeah!

14:10.416 --> 14:13.250
Now let's do the pyramid.

14:13.319 --> 14:16.453
Scootaloo get up
there; you're the top!

14:16.522 --> 14:21.125
You really do got yourself your
very own mega fans! Lucky you.

14:21.194 --> 14:22.593
[groan]

14:22.662 --> 14:27.698
♪♪

14:27.767 --> 14:29.534
[groan]

14:33.006 --> 14:35.706
You hung that towel! YEAH!

14:35.775 --> 14:38.642
Greatest towel
hanger OF ALL TIME!

14:38.711 --> 14:46.016
TOWEL! TOWEL!
TOWEL! TOWEL!

14:46.085 --> 14:47.484
STOP!

14:47.553 --> 14:52.489
This is ridiculous! Mom and Dad,
you are both too supportive!

14:52.558 --> 14:55.292
This is exactly why I didn't
tell you I was a Wonderbolt;

14:55.361 --> 14:57.661
you're just too much!

14:57.730 --> 15:00.230
Did we do something wrong?

15:00.299 --> 15:02.733
Yes! The fireworks,
the cheerleading

15:02.802 --> 15:06.036
and how do you even compare
who is better or worse

15:06.105 --> 15:07.639
at hanging up a towel?!

15:09.108 --> 15:11.375
We're just trying
to be supportive.

15:11.444 --> 15:14.044
Well, I'm tired of it! I've
had enough of you two

15:14.113 --> 15:16.280
being so proud of every
little ridiculous,

15:16.349 --> 15:18.349
insignificant thing I do!

15:18.418 --> 15:20.051
[panting]

15:21.788 --> 15:24.521
I think you should leave.

15:24.590 --> 15:28.192
First of all, great job
yelling at us, sweetie.

15:28.261 --> 15:33.530
No one can make their parents
feel more worthless than you.

15:33.599 --> 15:38.736
Your words were direct,
clear and... so painful.

15:38.805 --> 15:41.138
Is there nothing
you can't do?

15:41.207 --> 15:43.674
[blubbering]

15:43.743 --> 15:45.476
Why?

15:45.545 --> 15:48.445
Scootaloo, you
don't understand.

15:48.514 --> 15:51.515
I met your parents hoping
to learn more about you

15:51.584 --> 15:53.451
but I don't like
what I found out.

15:55.455 --> 15:58.589
I'll find somepony else
to do my hero report on.

15:58.658 --> 16:04.662
♪♪

16:10.369 --> 16:12.403
Scootaloo, wait!

16:12.472 --> 16:14.271
I know I wasn't
myself back there

16:14.340 --> 16:16.507
and I shouldn't have
snapped at my parents.

16:16.576 --> 16:20.310
But that's exactly why I didn't
tell them I'm a Wonderbolt.

16:20.379 --> 16:23.714
I don't understand;
they're so proud of you.

16:23.783 --> 16:25.215
[sigh]

16:25.284 --> 16:27.084
Can I tell you something?

16:27.153 --> 16:28.386
Sure.

16:28.454 --> 16:30.454
OK, but you might want
to hold onto your wings

16:30.523 --> 16:33.725
because this could rock
you to your very core.

16:38.164 --> 16:39.797
Believe it or not,
there was a time

16:39.866 --> 16:42.399
when I wasn't the
best at everything.

16:42.468 --> 16:44.635
[gasp]

16:44.704 --> 16:48.505
See this picture? It looks
like I won something awesome.

16:48.574 --> 16:51.108
But, actually...

16:51.177 --> 16:53.277
Announcer: And last but not
least, it's time to hand out

16:53.346 --> 16:55.179
our participant stickers.

16:55.248 --> 16:59.149
♪♪

16:59.218 --> 17:06.224
Yeah! Rainbow Dash,
you show them!

17:06.659 --> 17:10.127
Greatest participant ever!

17:10.196 --> 17:12.597
Your parents realize you
didn't win, don't they?

17:15.535 --> 17:18.335
Granted, I was the youngest pony

17:18.404 --> 17:20.504
in the senior
competitive circuit.

17:20.573 --> 17:22.172
Most other ponies my age

17:22.241 --> 17:24.808
were still in the
junior flappers club.

17:24.877 --> 17:27.411
I thought it was
utterly mortifying

17:27.480 --> 17:30.781
having my parents cheer
me on even when I lost.

17:30.850 --> 17:33.484
But then when I started
to win competitions,

17:33.553 --> 17:35.853
which didn't take
very long, by the way,

17:35.922 --> 17:38.689
things got even worse.

17:38.758 --> 17:42.259
Woo!! Yeah! Go Rainbow!
Go Rainbow! Woohoo!

17:42.328 --> 17:45.629
Yeah, Rainbow Dash! You
show em! That's our girl!

17:45.698 --> 17:47.798
Being the best came
with consequences.

17:47.867 --> 17:51.202
Very loud, very
embarrassing consequences.

17:52.538 --> 17:53.404
[sigh]

17:53.472 --> 17:55.739
You know, some
ponies would dream

17:55.808 --> 17:57.574
of having parents
like that.

17:57.643 --> 18:01.145
Yeah, right, name one.

18:01.214 --> 18:06.350
Me. Growing up, I never thought
I'd be the best at anything

18:06.419 --> 18:09.153
because no pony ever told me.

18:09.222 --> 18:12.923
But your parents told you
over and over again -- look.

18:12.992 --> 18:18.328
Best bath taker ever. Best
carrot eater under three.

18:18.397 --> 18:21.498
Greatest napper of all time!

18:21.567 --> 18:25.302
I am pretty good at napping.
I can fall asleep anywhere.

18:25.371 --> 18:28.839
[snoring]

18:28.908 --> 18:29.874
Huh?

18:31.010 --> 18:33.577
For your entire life,
your parents gave you

18:33.646 --> 18:35.546
the confidence to
believe in yourself.

18:39.685 --> 18:43.954
You're right. I was always
so embarrassed by my parents

18:44.023 --> 18:46.823
that I didn't realize their
support actually made me

18:46.892 --> 18:49.893
the awesome, confident,
amazing, awesome

18:49.962 --> 18:51.762
and awesome pony I am.

18:54.967 --> 18:57.935
And I took them for granted.

18:58.004 --> 18:59.803
And you yelled
at them.

18:59.872 --> 19:02.206
Ugh, I gotta make
this right.

19:04.677 --> 19:07.411
I have an idea, but I'm
going to need your help.

19:07.480 --> 19:10.548
That is, if you're willing to
help me after I acted like that.

19:12.852 --> 19:14.818
Now that's a great picture.

19:14.887 --> 19:17.522
Rainbow Dash learns
the error of her ways.

19:20.293 --> 19:23.260
I'm telling you, I just
can't see a thing!

19:23.329 --> 19:26.396
Scootaloo, you are just
so great at blindfolds.

19:26.465 --> 19:29.600
It's true. You must tell me
what kind of knot you used.

19:29.669 --> 19:32.803
A Falconer's knot? Wait
no... a farmer's loop!

19:32.872 --> 19:35.539
What's this
all about, anyhoo?

19:35.608 --> 19:38.742
Rainbow over loudspeaker: Windy
Whistles and Bow Hothoof,

19:38.811 --> 19:42.913
please be seated for a super
private Wonderbolt event.

19:42.982 --> 19:52.422
♪♪

19:52.491 --> 19:53.724
Ahem.

19:53.793 --> 19:56.026
Mom and Dad, welcome to the

19:56.095 --> 19:57.494
"I love my parents and
I'm sorry that I took them

19:57.563 --> 19:59.630
for granted and I know that
they made me who I am today

19:59.699 --> 20:01.699
so I really want to make
it up to them" event.

20:04.937 --> 20:05.870
Enjoy.

20:11.344 --> 20:12.409
Thanks for doing this.

20:12.478 --> 20:13.677
Happy to help!

20:13.746 --> 20:18.849
[whoosh]

20:18.918 --> 20:21.953
Ooooh! Aaaaah!

20:38.838 --> 20:43.073
Mom and Dad, I want you to know
that I'm your biggest fan.

20:43.142 --> 20:45.842
♪♪

20:45.911 --> 20:50.647
Oh, honey, thank you. But you
didn't have to do all this.

20:50.716 --> 20:53.917
It's kind of... embarrassing.

20:53.986 --> 20:55.820
Yeah, it is a bit much.

20:57.656 --> 20:59.456
And that's why Rainbow Dash

20:59.525 --> 21:02.559
is the most inspirational
pony in my life.

21:02.628 --> 21:04.961
[knocking]

21:05.030 --> 21:07.898
Thank you, Scootaloo.
Very well researched,

21:07.967 --> 21:09.900
but a little heavy
on the pictures

21:09.969 --> 21:13.337
and there was a moldy
sandwich in your report.

21:13.406 --> 21:14.871
I'll give you a B.

21:14.940 --> 21:19.343
YEAH! GREATEST
REPORT-GIVER OF ALL TIME!

21:19.412 --> 21:24.581
SCOOT-AL-LOO! SCOOT-AL-LOO!
SCOOT-AL-LOO!

21:24.650 --> 21:28.785
Keep it down! OK, this isn't
a rock and roll concert!

21:28.854 --> 21:30.721
Please!
